[normal]Written Evidence Submitted by the [bold] [bold]Migrant &amp;[bold] Refugee Children’s Legal Unit ([bold]MiCLU[bold])[bold] and [bold]Islington Law Centre[bold] (ILC) (LAI 0072)[bold]MiCLU
[normal] and ILC welcome the Joint Committee on Human Rights’ 
[normal](JCHR) 
[normal]inquiry into the effect on access to justice of the changes to the legal aid regime proposed by the 
[normal]coalition 
[normal]government in 
[normal]‘
[normal]Transforming Legal Aid: 
[normal]Delivering 
[normal]a 
[normal]More Credible 
[normal]and 
[normal]Efficient 
[normal]System’
[normal] 
[normal]and now revised in 
[normal]‘
[normal]Transforming Legal Aid: Next 
[normal]Steps’
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]We have grave concerns regarding the effect of these proposals on access to justice for 
[normal]the most vulnerable in our society, including 
[normal]children, young people
[normal], 
[normal]vulnerable adults, 
[normal]and 
[normal]those who 
[normal]do not have the means to fund legal advice to ensure that their fundamental human rights are protected
[normal]. 
