[normal]Lisa is 17 year old South African national. She arrived with her mother on a visit visa when she was a small child. Her 
[normal]mother overstays her visa and whilst in the UK she gives birth to Lisa’s younger sister 
[normal]Noeleen
[normal]. Lisa’s mother is an alcoholic and a drug addict. The Local Authority have concerns over the mother’s ability to 
[normal]care for 
[normal]Noeleen
[normal], who is 5 years old at the tim
[normal]e, and she is taken into Local Authority care. Lisa remains with her mother. Lisa’s mother dies due to her drug and alcohol problems. Following her mother’s death Lisa goes to the Local Authority to tell them what happens and ask for help. They fail to pro
[normal]vide her with support and accommodation and Lisa is homeless although a school friend has allowed her to sleep on her sofa for a few nights.
